      "content": "No, self-treating a condition requiring blood tests to remain safe is not advised, and ramping up supplements like garlic can dangerously lower your INR too quickly. Warfarin's effects fluctuate with diet, so guessing dosage based on \"natural\" intake without lab results puts your life at extreme risk. Please consult a blood-thinner specialist to find a safer plan that gives you more control than blindly following unverified advice.",
