    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it just feels like such a huge burden. i mean, i see so many people talking about how much better they feel when they go all-natural and ditch the pharmaceuticals. if i were to just start taking a very high dose of garlic extract—like 2000mg or something—and drinking a kale smoothie every single morning, wouldn't that provide a much more stable way to keep my blood thin without the constant spikes and dips you get from the pills? it seems more consistent to just use what's in nature.",
