      "content": "No, garlic and kale are not dependable substitutes for warfarin because their effects on your blood thinning vary too much from day to day to manage safely without monitoring. Using high-dose supplements alongside your current medication or trying to taper off abruptly can cause sudden, dangerous drops in your clotting ratio, leading to internal bleeding that doctors cannot track. You need to speak with a hematologist who understands natural interactions, as they can create a supervised plan that respects your desire for control while keeping you safe.",
